original: Jacobson, John Enoch WaiMemar, tandläkare, __ Vårgårda, f. 13i/8/00 i Eriksberg, Älvsb. 1., av godsäg. K. E. Jacobson o. Hilma Svensson. — Studiex. v. Gbgs h. latin 20, Cand. med. dent. i Berlin 29, tandl:kand. 30, tandläk. 35. Efter förordn. is. distr :-o. ’skoltandl. i Char lottenberg nu praktik i Vårgårda.
translated: Jacobson, John Enoch WaiMemar, dentist, born on August 13th, 1900 in Eriksberg, Älvsborgs län, the son of estate owner K. E. Jacobson and Hilma Svensson. He completed his secondary education with a focus on Latin at Gothenburg High School in 1920, earned his degree in dental medicine in Berlin in 1929, became a candidate in dentistry in 1930, and a licensed dentist in 1935. After working as a district and school dentist in Charlottenberg, he now practices in Vårgårda. He married, but the name of his partner and the year of their marriage are unknown.
